the  national taiwan museum  is the oldest museum in  taiwan  it was set up by the colonial government of  japan  on october 24 1908 to commemorate the inauguration of the northsouth railway during the  japanese rule in taiwan  the colonial government of japan set up the taiwan governor museum  the museum had a collection of over 10000 items in its initial stages in 1915 the new building of the museum in taipei new park was inaugurated and became one of the major public buildings during  japanese rule
